org.eng.aisp.feature.processor.vector

Class MagnitudeFeatureProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eng.aisp.processor.GenericCachingDataProcessor
      • org.eng.aisp.feature.processor.AbstractCachingMultiFeatureProcessor<double[]>
        • org.eng.aisp.feature.processor.vector.MagnitudeFeatureProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IFeatureProcessor<double[]>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    L1MagnitudeFeatureProcessor, LpMagnitudeFeatureProcessor

    public class MagnitudeFeatureProcessor
extends AbstractCachingMultiFeatureProcessor<double[]>
    Uses a distance metric to compute the magnitude of the features. Magnitude may be computed within a feature or across feature elements. The magnitudes may optionally be averaged to single value. For a NxM (time x feature len) feature gram,
    • If computing across time, the result will be a 1xM feature gram.
    • If computing across each feature, the result will be a Nx1 feature gram.
    • If averaging everything, the result will be a 1x1 feature gram.
    Author:
    DavidWood
